Valene.GovenderPhoto: supplied Soul Buddyz members who raised funds for the childhood cancer organisation. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories THE vibrant buddyz of Buffelsdale Primary s Soul Buddyz Club took the initiative to raise funds for a worthy course. In South Africa one in 600 children is affected by cancer. The buddyz handed over R2500 to Agie Govender, a representative from Choc. Govender was overwhelmed by the enthusiastic buddyz who always offer a helping hand towards community projects. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.